reviews.text: Slow service (waited over an hour to receive first dish) but the food is fine.

We have frequented this family run restaurant many times.  A popular place with mainly repeat customers. They have genuine home cooking and use only fresh ingredients and the portions are always very generous. Our favorite dishes are sautéed  clams in black pepper sauce and their
house special chicken hotpot.  The restaurant is only open in the evenings and seating is limited.  Be sure to make reservations in advance to avoid disappointment.
